attachmentNetworkAclConfigurations.description: Rules that define how you manage outbound traffic from kdb network to your internal network. Defined below.

routableCidrSpace.description: Routing CIDR on behalf of KX environment. It could be any “/26 range in the 100.64.0.0 CIDR space. After providing, it will be added to the customer’s transit gateway routing table so that the traffics could be routed to KX network.

transitGatewayId.description: Identifier of the transit gateway created by the customer to connect outbound traffics from KX network to your internal network.
